      <h1 class='title'>Disability Rights Commission</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 21 July 2004 vol 424 c54WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_54ws' title='Col. 54WS &mdash; HC Deb 21 July 2004 vol 424 c54WS' name='column_54ws' href='#column_54ws' rel='bookmark'>54WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040721_CWS_38'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-smith' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040721_CWS_38' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew Smith' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-smith" title="Mr Andrew Smith">The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions (Mr. Andrew Smith)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Disability Rights Commission's annual report and accounts 2003&#x2013;04 have been published today and laid before Parliament. The DRC's annual report of its activities in 2003&#x2013;04 details considerable success in its work to eliminate discrimination against disabled people; promote equal opportunities; encourage good practice and keep the working of the <a href="/acts/disability-discrimination-act-1995">Disability Discrimination Act</a> and the <a href="/acts/drc-act">DRC Act</a> under review.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
